The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The focus is on sparsity-promoting reconstruction using $\ell^1$-penalized least-squares reconstruction, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves statistical decision theory, which is a topic in mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Finally, the paper evaluates the worst-case asymptotic minimax mean-squared reconstruction error, which involves optimization and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
